step1 --> start your terminal or commmand pormpt

step2 --->install git(by following steps )

         step(a)-->in terminal-->pip install git  (if you use python)
                         or      sudo apt-get install git  (linux)
                         or      go to git website and simply download and install  it (windows)
         step(b)--->git config --global user.name "yourname"
         step(c)--->git config --global user.email "your email"




Now initialize or add git repository
step3-->go to your desire dirictory (###for example where your code save (in terminal ----cd Desktop/mydir/allfile))

       then initialize or add git repository
  step4 --> git init
  step5 --> git status 
  step6 --> git add -A
  step7 --> git commmit -m 'initial commit'
  
CHoose you git repository to save your code
